+ Fix the version numbers in files:

    vi Dockerfile

    Dockerfile
        search for 'org.label-schema.schema-version='


+ Edit CHANGELOG.md (use git log to get the history)

+ Sync everything to github.

+ Create a new tag (instructions from https://git-scm.com/book/en/v2/Git-Basics-Tagging) 
  and push to github:

    git tag -a v2.0alpha3 -m "v2.0alpha3"
    git push origin v2.0alpha3


+ Edit the release notes on github

+ Build and sync new docker images

    builddocker.sh
